The South African documentary My Octopus Teacher gets a Bafta nod (Twitter @TvMzansi) JOHANNESBURG - A South African production bagged the Bafta award for best documentary. My Octopus Teacher documents the filmmaker's relationship with a wild octopus in the Western Cape. It is directed by Pippa Ehrlich and James Reed and aired on Netflix. READ: Tina Turner bids farewell to fans with emotional new doc The 74th British Academy Film award ceremony was broadcast from London's Albert Hall. But due to COVID-19 restrictions there was no audience. The documentary is also tipped for an Oscar.